TWO bodies believed to be those of a missing couple were found inside a car at Unicor Dam in Evander near Secunda, Mpumalanga, on Friday. According to provincial police spokesman Brigadier Leonard Hlathi, the discovery was made by police divers from Secunda and Delta 1 Rescue team. “Cops spotted a VW Citi Golf in the belly of the dam with two bodies inside. “It was discovered that the vehicle belongs to Siyabonga Nkabi, who was reported missing on 4 July. He was with Precious Mtsweni at the time of the disappearance. “At this stage, cops can’t confirm if the bodies are those of the missing couple because of their condition. “The next of kin have been informed of the discovery. But the outcome of the investigation will be a determining factor,” he said.